      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Skills Gap Strategy Act of 2013 - Directs the Secretary of Labor to develop a strategy report to address the skills gap by providing analysis and recommendations to increase on-the-job training and apprenticeship opportunities, identify industry-recognized postsecondary credentials that are nationally portable and aligned with in-demand occupations in industries such as construction, manufacturing, and others that are emerging, and increase employer participation in education and workforce training.</p> <p>Defines the term &quot;skills gap&quot; as the difference, or gap, between the current supply of labor and skills of the workforce and that which is desired by employers.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2013-10-30T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2013-12-04T16:10:47Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDate>2013-10-30</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
